Protoconch (eroded in the 
holotype
) of 2.7+ whorls, 660 Μm high and 720 Μm wide at the base. Protoconch-II of about 2.5 whorls, with 2 spiral keels, sculptured with a series of subsutural threads and a series of oblong tubercles over each keel. A diffuse granulation is present in the interspaces.
